de.rincewind.api.gui.elements

Interface ElementInput

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Element, ElementSlot, EventBased
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CraftElementInput, Elements.ElementInputExtendable

    public interface ElementInput
extends ElementSlot
    In this element, the user can put items in, and pickup items already dropped in the slot. You are able to inject the item into the cache.
    Since:
    2.3.3
    Author:
    Rincewind34
    See Also:
    Elements.ElementInputExtendable

        int lastIndex()
        Returns the index of the latest injected item. If there was no item injected already, the result will be -1.
        Returns:
        the index of the latest injected item

      • inject

        org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack inject()
        Injects the item, witch is present in the slot. If the slot is empty, this method will return null. If there is an item in the slot, the item will be removed and the item will be added to the memory.
        Returns:
        the item, witch is present in the slot
